<subSubSection lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="110" pageId="30" pageNumber="109" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="109">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="110" pageId="30" pageNumber="109">
The type is badly damaged by dermestids. It lacks the antennae, the right part of the head, including mouthparts and occipitum and the right foreleg. Together with this type there are two other specimens ([NHRS-HEVA000001134] and [NHRS-HEVA000001135]) collected in the same locality by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sjöstedt">Sjoestedt</normalizedToken>
and on Mount Meru, but to be excluded from the type-series because they were collected on different days. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cameron, P" journalOrPublisher="Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Schwedischen zoologischen Expedition nach dem Kilimandjaro, dem Meru und den umgebenden Massaisteppen Deutsch-Ostafrikas 1905 - 1906" pageId="43" pageNumber="122" pagination="297 - 299" refId="B14" refString="Cameron, P, 1910. Chrysididae. Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Schwedischen zoologischen Expedition nach dem Kilimandjaro, dem Meru und den umgebenden Massaisteppen Deutsch-Ostafrikas 1905-1906 2: 297 - 299" title="Chrysididae." volume="2" year="1910">Cameron (1910)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum massaicum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="massaicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">
<pageBreakToken pageId="31" pageNumber="110" start="start">Hedychrum</pageBreakToken>
massaicum
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based only on the specimen collected on the 2nd of November. The other two specimens have been collected the 6th of September and in January. French identified all of them as 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum massaicum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="massaicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Hedychrum massaicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but one of the specimens [175 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">85</emphasis>
] collected in January belongs to a different species. Bohart (
<bibRefCitation author="Kimsey, LS" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, New York" pageId="45" pageNumber="124" refId="B37" refString="Kimsey, LS, Bohart, RM, 1991 1990. The Chrysidid Wasps of the World. Oxford University Press, New York" title="The Chrysidid Wasps of the World." year="1991">Kimsey and Bohart 1991</bibRefCitation>
: 216) examined the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“holotype”">&quot;holotype&quot;</normalizedToken>
deposited at the MZLU, but this specimen was not found, and all the material collected by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sjöstedt">Sjoestedt</normalizedToken>
is deposited at the NHRS.
</paragraph>
